==English==
===Etymology===
From [[factor]] + [[-ize]]
===Alternative spellings===
*(''mainly British''): [[factorise]]
===Verb===
{{en-verb|factorize|factorizing|factorized|factorized}}

#{{mathematics}}: To [[create]] a [[list]] of [[factor]]s.
#{{mathematics}}: To divide an [[expression]] into a listing items that, when [[multiply|multiplied]] together, will produce the original quantity.

